In[119]:
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Get probability scores for the positive class
y_score_lr = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

# Calculate False Positive Rate and True Positive Rate
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_score_lr)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)

# Plot ROC curve
plt.figure(figsize=(7, 5))
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, color='green', lw=2, label=f'Logistic Regression (AUC = {roc_auc:.2f})')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='gray', linestyle='--')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve - Logistic Regression')
plt.legend(loc='lower right')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Get probabilities
lr_probs = lr_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
rf_probs = rf_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
xgb_probs = xgb_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

# Calculate ROC curve and AUC
fpr_lr, tpr_lr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, lr_probs)
fpr_rf, tpr_rf, _ = roc_curve(y_test, rf_probs)
fpr_xgb, tpr_xgb, _ = roc_curve(y_test, xgb_probs)

auc_lr = auc(fpr_lr, tpr_lr)
auc_rf = auc(fpr_rf, tpr_rf)
auc_xgb = auc(fpr_xgb, tpr_xgb)

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(fpr_lr, tpr_lr, label=f"Logistic (AUC = {auc_lr:.2f})", color='blue')
plt.plot(fpr_rf, tpr_rf, label=f"Random Forest (AUC = {auc_rf:.2f})", color='green')
plt.plot(fpr_xgb, tpr_xgb, label=f"XGBoost (AUC = {auc_xgb:.2f})", color='red')
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
plt.title('ROC Curve Comparison')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
